  "texts": [
    "The distance between WVS answers and the LLM central tendency, that we call centerEMD, functions as a counterfactual: it represents the value that the LLM's prediction error would have if the LLM was completely unresponsive to variations in socio-demographics.",
    "In such a case, LLM prediction errors would be driven by the socio-demographic variations of the ground-truth WVS answer patterns only.",
    "Figure 5 illustrates this counterfactual reasoning, aimed at isolating the effect of social controls on the LLM answers.",
    "The Center model regresses LLM prediction errors only on the counterfactual centerEMD, the Full model both on the counterfactual and on the social controls.",
    "The former measures how much of LLM prediction error can be attributed to low LLM dispersion alone, the latter the relative contributions of low dispersion and social controls."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}